Hey Maverick I've made a business out of this space we used to be coaches for crypto coins and tokens and always had an interest in the Metaverse and the P2E model so with the rise we've concentrated our efforts in this space now It's a very interesting time most ready to play P2E games are pretty dull and don't look very good but their popularity nets pretty huge returns I'm more interested in AAA titles being an avid gamer and former competitive gamer so projects like this suit me more but it's VERY early days for all of these kinds of titles most are in their Alpha and Beta stages some even Pre-Alpha so there are bugs and the like As with traditional alpha and beta games though those testers will be the ones most rewarded in the future and with monetary value tied to these specific games you can be fairly certain those rewards in the future will distribute a huge amount of wealth I'm yet to play this game but it looks very promising I will say this though ANY game with real world value economies are incredibly complex and have a steep learning curve while difficult if you can learn to master these and spend your time learning each game's specific economy you will come out in the top tier of earners The biggest thing is to have fun if you don't enjoy the game it will be just like work and you'll get bored and under perform that's why I stay with the larger titles to keep engaged and enjoy my job Hope this helps

---------------------------------- Fees on Solana or Star Atlas ---------------------------------- Hope you have chosen a faction and want to buy ship Before that please have 0.2 SOL in your wallet apart from the ship cost This is for trading pair deposits and a few basic transactions. Why is the fee so high Actually its not here's the thing Solana is decentralized and uses Serum DEX for trading Star Atlas merely uses Serum DEX for marketplace behind the scene. You pay 0.023 for each trading pair for Serum and this is refundable if you decide to stop playing So there are trading pairs for Ships and Each of the 4 resources food fuel ammo and tools So 0.092 SOL for buying each resource your ship trading pair deposit 0.115 SOL actual ship cost in USDC/Atlas The 0.092 SOL you paid for resources is one-time only subsequent transactions to buy resources cost merely 0.000005 SOL tx fee apart from the resource cost. Whenever you want you can get a refund for these trading pair deposits on https://sonar.watch/tools/serum-dex under accounts you can cancel This does not affect your existing purchases but not recommended as it can cause some issues while withdrawing fleets Suggest to get a refund only when you decide to stop playing. Remember though if you cancel on sonar.watch the next time you want to buy any resource you pay the same trading pair deposit again.

Fees on Solana or Star Atlas ---------------------------------- Hope you have chosen a faction and want to buy ship Before that please have 0.2 SOL in your wallet apart from the ship cost This is for trading pair deposits and a few basic transactions. Why is the fee so high Actually its not here's the thing Solana is decentralized and uses Serum DEX for trading Star Atlas merely uses Serum DEX for marketplace behind the scene. You pay 0.023 for each trading pair for Serum and this is refundable if you decide to stop playing So there are trading pairs for Ships and Each of the 4 resources food fuel ammo and tools So 0.092 SOL for buying each resource your ship trading pair deposit 0.115 SOL actual ship cost in USDC/Atlas The 0.092 SOL you paid for resources is one-time only subsequent transactions to buy resources cost merely 0.000005 SOL tx fee apart from the resource cost. Whenever you want you can get a refund for these trading pair deposits on https://sonar.watch/tools/serum-dex under accounts you can cancel This does not affect your existing purchases but not recommended as it can cause some issues while withdrawing fleets Suggest to get a refund only when you decide to stop playing. Remember though if you cancel on sonar.watch the next time you want to buy any resource you pay the same trading pair deposit again.

For USA people The taxes you own on the remaining 900 rely on two things You have two different events you have to consider How much it was worth when you received it and then how much it was worth when you traded it or sold it Event #1 The moment you claim your Atlas and it goes into your wallet is when you have made a taxable event and you owe standard income tax on the value of that claim Event #2 When you sell it you owe either short or long term capital gains taxes on the higher price it may be when you sell or a capital loss on the lower price it is from when you claimed it I will be selling or trading my ATLAS from staking instantly after each monthly claim That way the difference in price between when I claimed it and when I sold it is virtually zero See how much fun the US Tax system makes things?

Basics applying to the question about taxes The ATLAS required for resources is like a business expense or selling fee Generic number example You earn 1000 atlas a month You spent 100 of that ATLAS on resources You figure your taxes over the remaining 900.

Fees on Solana or Star Atlas ---------------------------------- Hope you have chosen a faction and want to buy ship Before that please have 0.2 SOL in your wallet apart from the ship cost This is for trading pair deposits and a few basic transactions. Why is the fee so high Actually its not here's the thing Solana is decentralized and uses Serum DEX for trading Star Atlas merely uses Serum DEX for marketplace behind the scene. You pay 0.023 for each trading pair for Serum and this is refundable if you decide to stop playing So there are trading pairs for Ships and Each of the 4 resources food fuel ammo and tools So 0.092 SOL for buying each resource your ship trading pair deposit 0.115 SOL actual ship cost in USDC/Atlas The 0.092 SOL you paid for resources is one-time only subsequent transactions to buy resources cost merely 0.000005 SOL tx fee apart from the resource cost. Whenever you want you can get a refund for these trading pair deposits on https://sonar.watch/tools/serum-dex under accounts you can cancel This does not affect your existing purchases but not recommended as it can cause some issues while withdrawing fleets Suggest to get a refund only when you decide to stop playing. Remember though if you cancel on sonar.watch the next time you want to buy any resource you pay the same trading pair deposit again.

here's a bit of info on the fees: SOLANA FEES: ---------------------------------- Fees on Solana or Star Atlas ---------------------------------- Hope you have chosen a faction and want to buy ship Before that please have 0.2 SOL in your wallet apart from the ship cost This is for trading pair deposits and a few basic transactions. Why is the fee so high Actually its not here's the thing Solana is decentralized and uses Serum DEX for trading Star Atlas merely uses Serum DEX for marketplace behind the scene. You pay 0.023 for each trading pair for Serum and this is refundable if you decide to stop playing So there are trading pairs for Ships and Each of the 4 resources food fuel ammo and tools So 0.092 SOL for buying each resource your ship trading pair deposit 0.115 SOL actual ship cost in USDC/Atlas The 0.092 SOL you paid for resources is one-time only subsequent transactions to buy resources cost merely 0.000005 SOL tx fee apart from the resource cost. Whenever you want you can get a refund for these trading pair deposits on https://sonar.watch/tools/serum-dex under accounts you can cancel This does not affect your existing purchases but not recommended as it can cause some issues while withdrawing fleets Suggest to get a refund only when you decide to stop playing. Remember though if you cancel on sonar.watch the next time you want to buy any resource you pay the same trading pair deposit again.

Just wanted to make some points I do both I think both have pro and con). 1 yield the yield you see on Tulip for $atlas (currently say 80% is **APY** It means you have to hold from now compounding for the whole year It is not APR It is not the same. If you buy ships and stake these are static APR yields Say Jetjet netting 56% If you have a big enough bag claiming emissions every day and rolling into smaller ships which in turn have yield Or compounding into Tulip Your APY becomes substantially higher than 56 APR Again depending on if you have a big bag or not If its just 1 Airbike then forget it. 2 Liquidity and Counterparty remember if you play on Francium or Tulip you have counterparty risk Team rugs youâ€™re REKT If you leverage you also have smart contract risk Exploit on your contract youâ€™re REKT If there is artificial flash-crash or flash-dump on $atlas and you leveraged youâ€™re liquidated and REKT If you want to sell out for whatever liquidity reason you have and $atlas utilization is over 95% you cannot withdraw You are stuck and possibly REKT.

Fees on Solana or Star Atlas ---------------------------------- Hope you have chosen a faction and want to buy ship Before that please have 0.2 SOL in your wallet apart from the ship cost This is for trading pair deposits and a few basic transactions. Why is the fee so high Actually its not here's the thing Solana is decentralized and uses Serum DEX for trading Star Atlas merely uses Serum DEX for marketplace behind the scene. You pay 0.023 for each trading pair for Serum and this is refundable if you decide to stop playing So there are trading pairs for Ships and Each of the 4 resources food fuel ammo and tools So 0.092 SOL for buying each resource your ship trading pair deposit 0.115 SOL actual ship cost in USDC/Atlas The 0.092 SOL you paid for resources is one-time only subsequent transactions to buy resources cost merely 0.000005 SOL tx fee apart from the resource cost. Whenever you want you can get a refund for these trading pair deposits on https://sonar.watch/tools/serum-dex under accounts you can cancel This does not affect your existing purchases but not recommended as it can cause some issues while withdrawing fleets Suggest to get a refund only when you decide to stop playing. Remember though if you cancel on sonar.watch the next time you want to buy any resource you pay the same trading pair deposit again.
